definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  4-maleylacetoacetate -eq- 4-fumarylacetoacetate.

A heterodimeric DNA polymerase complex that catalyzes error-prone DNA synthesis in contexts such as translesion synthesis and double-stranded break repair. First characterized in Saccharomyces, in which the subunits are Rev3p and Rev7p -  a third protein, Rev1p, is often associated with the polymerase dimer.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2 L-glutamate + NAD(+) -eq- 2-oxoglutarate + L-glutamine + H(+) + NADH.

Catalysis of the reaction -  2 L-glutamate + 2 oxidized ferredoxin -eq- L-glutamine + 2-oxoglutarate + 2 reduced ferredoxin + 2 H+. This is a two-step reaction -  (a) L-glutamate + NH3 -eq- L-glutamine + H2O, (b) L-glutamate + 2 oxidized ferredoxin + H2O -eq- NH3 + 2-oxoglutarate + 2 reduced ferredoxin + 2 H+.
The action characteristic of myostimulatory hormone, a peptide hormone that stimulates muscle contraction.
The action characteristic of myostimulatory hormone, a peptide hormone that inhibits muscle contraction.
The action characteristic of ecdysiostatic hormone, a peptide hormone that inhibits ecdysone secretion.

label.value: translation release factor activity, codon specific

definition.value: A translation release factor that is specific for one or more particular termination codons -  acts at the ribosomal A-site and require polypeptidyl-tRNA at the P-site.

label.value: translation release factor activity, codon nonspecific

definition.value: A translation release factor that is not specific to particular codons -  binds to guanine nucleotides.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with nickel (Ni) cations.
Catalysis of the reaction -  H(+) + Hg + NADP(+) -eq- Hg(2+) + NADPH.
Catalysis of the reaction -  4-imidazolone-5-propanoate + H(+) -eq- trans-urocanate + H(2)O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  pyrimidine nucleoside + phosphate -eq- pyrimidine + alpha-D-ribose 1-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  10-formyltetrahydrofolate + H(2)O + NADP(+) -eq- (6S)-5,6,7,8-tetrahydrofolate + CO(2) + H(+) + NADPH.
Catalysis of the reaction -  NAD(+) + succinate -eq- fumarate + H(+) + NADH.
Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-glucose + D-fructose -eq- UDP + sucrose.
Catalysis of the reaction -  myo-inositol hexakisphosphate + H2O -eq- D-myo-inositol 1,2,4,5,6-pentakisphosphate + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2,5-dihydro-5-oxofuran-2-acetate -eq- 3,4-dihydro-5-oxofuran-2-acetate.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of amylose or an amylose derivative.

Catalysis of the reaction -  (1,4-alpha-D-glucosyl)(n+1) + H2O -eq- (1,4-alpha-D-glucosyl)(n-1) + alpha-maltose. This reaction is the hydrolysis of 1,4-alpha-glucosidic linkages in polysaccharides so as to remove successive maltose units from the non-reducing ends of the chains.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of (1--gt-4)-beta-D-glucosidic linkages in cellulose and cellotetraose, releasing cellobiose from the non-reducing ends of the chains.
Catalysis of the reaction -  8 reduced ferredoxin + 8 H+ + nitrogen + 16 ATP -eq- 8 oxidized ferredoxin + 2 NH3 + 16 ADP + 16 phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  linoleate + O2 -eq- (9Z,11E)-(13S)-13-hydroperoxyoctadeca-9,11-dienoate.
Catalysis of the dehydrogenation of phytoene to produce a carotenoid intermediate such as phytofluene.

label.value: glial cell-derived neurotrophic factor receptor activity

definition.value: Combining with glial cell line-derived neurotrophic factor and transmitting the signal from one side of the membrane to the other to initiate a change in cell activity.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with chlorophyll -  any compound of magnesium complexed in a porphyrin (tetrapyrrole) ring and which functions as a photosynthetic pigment.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with bacteriochlorophyll c, a chlorophyll of photosynthetic bacteria, for example green sulfur bacteria.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the interleukin-15 receptor.
Catalysis of the reaction -  NAD(P)H + H+ + O2 -eq- NAD(P)+ + hydrogen peroxide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  NAD(P)H + O2 -eq- NAD(P)H + O2-.
Increases the activity of the enzyme superoxide-generating NADPH oxidase.
Catalysis of the reaction -  selenocysteine + S-adenosyl-L-methionine -eq- Se-methylselenocysteine + S-adenosyl-homocysteine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + a catechol -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + a guaiacol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + 4-coumarate + CoA -eq- AMP + diphosphate + 4-coumaroyl-CoA.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with AMP, adenosine monophosphate.

Inhibition of the reactions brought about by dioxygen (O2) or peroxides. Usually the antioxidant is effective because it can itself be more easily oxidized than the substance protected. The term is often applied to components that can trap free radicals, thereby breaking the chain reaction that normally leads to extensive biological damage.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3 malonyl-CoA + 4-coumaroyl-CoA -eq- 4 CoA + naringenin chalcone + 3 CO2.
Catalysis of the ligation of ammonia (NH3) to another substance via a carbon-nitrogen bond with concomitant breakage of a diphosphate linkage, usually in a nucleoside triphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-kynurenine + 2-oxoglutarate -eq- 4-(2-aminophenyl)-2,4-dioxobutanoate + L-glutamate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  linoleoyl-CoA + reduced acceptor + O2 -eq- gamma-linolenoyl-CoA + acceptor + 2 H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acyl-CoA + reduced acceptor + O2 -eq- desaturated-acyl-CoA + acceptor + 2 H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N-[(5S)-5-amino-5-carboxypentanoyl]-L-cysteinyl-D-valine + O(2) -eq- 2 H(2)O + isopenicillin N.
Catalysis of the reaction -  deethylsimazine + H2O -eq- N-ethylammeline + chloride + H+.

A protein complex that catalyzes the formation of procollagen trans-4-hydroxy-L-proline and succinate from procollagen L-proline and 2-oxoglutarate, requiring Fe2+ and ascorbate. Contains two alpha subunits that contribute to most parts of the catalytic sites, and two beta subunits that are identical to protein-disulfide isomerase.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-alanine + 2-oxopropanoate -eq- pyruvate + beta-alanine.
Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which one substrate is a sterol derivative.
Increases the activity of the enzyme sphingomyelin phosphodiesterase.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of terminal non-reducing N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residues in N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminides.

Catalysis of the synthesis of the HKK-1 carbohydrate epitope -  adds a sulfate group to a precursor, GlcA-beta-(1--gt-3)-Gal-beta-(1--gt-4)-GlcNAc-beta-(1--gt-R), forming sulfo-3GlcA-beta-(1--gt-3)-Gal-beta-(1--gt-4)-GlcNAc-beta-(1--gt-R).
A discrete intracellular part formed of aggregated molecules such as proteins or other biopolymers.
